                            <comment id="16137345" author="akolb" created="Tue, 22 Aug 2017 20:23:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that we should still understand old property if the new one isn&apos;t set and the old one is. Something like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (newProperty.isAvailable()) { use it }
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; { use old one }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16137351" author="vamsee" created="Tue, 22 Aug 2017 20:26:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the fact that we are releasing a new major version of Sentry, I think it is safe for us to break the compatibility in that aspect and make the code simpler by simply referring only to the new property. Any thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16137360" author="akolb" created="Tue, 22 Aug 2017 20:32:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it is safer to support old configs - this is the principle of least surprise - not breaking something that worked before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
